This paper deals with privacy amplification, which is a topic in computer security and machine learning. The paper discusses stochastic post-processing and Markov operators, which are concepts commonly used in information theory and probability theory. The paper also introduces a new family of mechanisms based on diffusion processes, which is a topic in statistical physics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
